                                          JAVA
                                          
    Array is used for fixed size collection of same type data. Array elements are accessed by index.
    indices are 0 based i.e. start from 0 and goes till arr.length-1.
 Note--- without index variable we can traverse array elements using foreach loop.
    Prefered way to create Array---
        dataType[] arrayRefVar = new dataType[arraySize];
        dataType[] arrayRefVar = {value0, value1, ..., valueN};
        
    Prefered way to declare array Variables----
        dataType[] arrayRefVar;